column2: Sunny- calm- algal bloom thick on shore.
Cloudy and windy.  Wind at 20 mph.

LAKE WATER     Cloudy- cool morning- 55 degrees air temp.  Only boat on the lake. Everyone is either resting or cleaning after company left for home and back to school.  Sure quiet.  Water is still very green along shoreline- better in middle of lake- due to cool temps.
Lake is about 95% weeds- hardly any big fish kill of crappies- clear of bloom.
Clear- sunny- and 60 degrees with a breeze.
Overcast sunny warm calm day 75 degrees.
Overcast hazy warm light wind 82 degrees.
Clear sunny warm light wind 78 degrees.

Dark- cloudy- cool- 10 mph wind from S- 65 F.
Bright- sunny- warm- 0 mph wind- 76 F- lake covered with algae.
Bright. Sunny. Cool. No wind. 60 F.
Partly sunny- no wind- temperature is 65 degrees- and algae mixed with water.
Sunny- calm- temperature is 80 degrees- and algae is collecting on the top.
Overcast- windy- temperature is 73 degrees- and algae mixed with water.
Northwest wind and algae mixed with water.
Clear- windy.  S wind.  Temp 85 F.

Clear sky- light SW wind- temp 75 F.  No floating algae.
Partly cloudy- NE wind.  Temp 67.  Heavy rain mixed floating algae.
Cloudy- light NE wind.  Temp 65.  No floating algae.
Calm- clear- temp 73. First algae along shore.

No wind- Temp. 60F- partly cloudy- 2" rain last night
temp. is 41 with aclear sky. water is very clear
lake is very low and quite green

column1: * bad membrane on DO meter

column2: Mostly cloudy- lake level below normal- water quality good- temp about 60- light breeze.  Secchi disk visible at 8 1/2 feet. Mostly cloudy- lake level below normal- water quality good- temp about 60- light breeze.  Secchi disk visible at 8 1/2 feet.  Do not have operating temp equipment. Mostly cloudy- lake level below normal- water quality good- temp about 60- light breeze.  Secchi disk visible at 8 1/2 feet.  Do not have operating temp equipment.
Clear skies- sunny- light winds- low lake level.
sunny- breezy- hot ~85F- lake ~15.9 feet deep
Temp 65- lake level very low- sunny- light winds.
Partly cloudy- hot- humid- water murky- greenish.  Helpers:  Grace Wheeler- Alex O'Connor.
sunny- windy- calm- pH meter ran out of batteries after surface reading
Cloudy- breezy- humid- 71 degrees.  Noticed a lot of large weed beds around lake perimeter.

Assisted by Phil Schaus from the University of Minnesota Agronomy Dept.  The weather is a beautiful sunshine morning with a temp of 73 and wind from the NW at 3mph.  A loon observed our testing.  The lake water was very green- esp. along the north shore- where it tended to take on the color and look of green oil based paint.
Saw 2 loons- 24 Canada geese- several eagles.  The skies were overcast- breezy- not much algae in the lake- but lots of weeds on the surface.
Lake is where it should be due to rainfall.  Water is brackish- but not full of algae.

column1: Skies partly sunny- temp 72.

column2: High water levels after 7+ inches of rain in 5 days.  Bright- sunny skies with no clouds- 73 degrees- slight breeze out of SW.  Water green.
Partly cloudy- calm- 65 degrees.  Observed 2 loons- several ducks- 4 Canada geese.  Joe Wheeler- my Grandson- assisted in temp recording and Secchi disk reading.
Sunny skies- absolutely beautiful morning.  62 degrees- winds sse 8 mph.  Observed 5 fishing boats and several families of Canada geese.  Assisted by Sandy Madsen.

Cloudy- breeze out of so.east- 2" of rain overnight into the mid-morning.  Sandy Madsen assisted with secchi test- temperature readings and water sample.  6 or 7 fishing boats on the lake.  Began thundering while testing- got more cloudy and appeared more rain on the way.  Probably affected secchi depth reading.

Overcast- hot and humid- 85 degrees. Wind from SW- pushing green surface algae to North shore.  Observed one loon- and several Canada geese at the farm. No geese seen on the lake.  3 other boats on lake.  No weeds above surface.
Cloudy- 80 degrees- 100% humidity.  Joe Wheeler(Grandson) and Dylan McCallum(Joe's buddy) helped with testing on the lake-  They observed several eagles soaring and fishing- and 4-5 fishing boats.
Cloudy- calm winds- 70 degree morning.  2 fishing boats on lake- couple of ducks.
cloudy- 2 boats on lake fishing - WI. fishing opener.  Not much activity either day.

column1: Observed 2-4 adult Canada geese and approx. 15 goslings on shore- nw side of lake.  Calm winds. Cloudy- received a lot of rain last night- approx. 1-1 1/2 ".  Calm winds- 2 fishing boats on lake- one left during observation.  One pontoon boat fishing at east end of lake.  54 degree air temp.  Observed 2-4 adult Canada geese and approx 15 goslings on shore- nw side of lake- grazing in green grass between road and lake. Cloudy- 54 degree air temp.- calm winds.  Cloudy afternoon- calm winds- only 2 fishing boats out on WI. opening weekend for fishing.  Observed 2-4 adult Canada geese and 10-12 goslings on nw shore- in grassy area between road and lake.

column2: Overcast- 75 degrees- calm winds- 6-8 fishing boats on lake.  No sign of Canada geese- which were present in great numbers on Sat.- 6-2.
Gorgeous day- partly cloudy. 78 degrees- NE wind.  10 fishing boats and 2 pontoons on lake.  Small flock of Canada geese- 4 adults- 6 young ones.
Partly cloudy- 90 degrees- light winds- not much activity on the lake.

column1: Flock of 40-50 Canada geese along north shore by farm.  No water monitoring helpers- but Brett Bartylla and Ben Kufalk are at boat landing inspecting boats for CB/CW program.

column2: Warm morning- slight breeze out of SE- flock of 15-20 Canada geese on lake in testing area.  Supported by son Gary- daughter in law Margaret- and grandson Henry.  Lake appeared exceptionally good for this time of year.  Very little algae or accumulation of weeds and floating stuff.
67 degrees- beautiful blue skies- light winds- no wildlife- 3 fishing boats on lake- green particles floating throughout lake
Mostly cloudy- calm winds- green color to water- few geese- 3 boats.
Beautiful- sunshine and blue skies.  Finally!!!  77 degrees- west winds 10mph- hundreds upon hundreds of dead fish in lake.  DNR in area credited fish kill to a fungus.

Beautiful morning- clouds gently gave way to full sun- 69 degrees- wsw 'wind' at 3 mph.  Flock of 10-15 Canada geese out from dock- population is miniscule compared to previous years.  Much appreciate the decline in geese on the lake this year- hoping it continues.  Lake had turned since last report 2 weeks ago- with many more surface weeds and a lot of green algae floating throughout.  One other boat on lake.
Parly cloudy- 72 degrees- humid- winds are calm- 4 fishing boats on lake.   Helpers were Henry Zuckweiler and Leo Zuckweiler.
Gorgeous morning- blue sky- slight breeze ENE- saw 2 loons- 20 fishing boats- flock of Canada geese- about 8-10 adults and same number of young ones.  64 degrees.  Perfect!

column1: Beautiful clear morning- 54 degrees- no wind-green algae floating across all of lake.  Guys had just finished spraying beach area for first time this summer.  Two fishing boats on lake.  Canada geese still cozying up on land.

column2: 75 degrees- partly cloudy- virtually no wind- beautiful morning.  Helpers were Henry and Leo Zuckweiler

column1: Beautiful sunny morning- 61 degrees- sw winds at 3mph.  Saw one loon- 4 Canada geese flying- 4 fishing boats.
Assisted by Grandsons Henry(6) and Leo(3yrs- 11mo.)

column2: 72 degrees- mostly sunny- wind nw at 9 mph.  Observed 12 boat trailers at landing- so lots of fishing going on this morning.
Quiet morning on the lake- mostly cloudy- 73 degrees.No wildlife observations this morning.
Beautiful sunny morning- very slight wind at 3-4 mph- 66 degrees air temp.  Several fishing boats out- no Canada geese on lake yet.
82 degrees- sunny very windy.  Assisted by Tim Wheeler
Did not receive vial and bottle with box this time- so only did water temp.

column1: Weather was 82 degrees- windy- overcast- storms on the way.

column2: Gorgeous morning- calm water- quiet except for one fishing boat.  Blue sky- no wind.

Sunny- winds East at 11.  No other boats on the lake- probably due to it being Mother's Day.  Previous day was one of the finest ever on the lake.  A late afternoon pontoon ride(5-6 pm) saw approx. 25 boaters on the lake actively fishing- There was no wind- and the water clarity allowed us to feel as though we were on top of an aquarium- with visibility about the best I have ever witnessed. Observed bass- crappie- northern- and other assorted panfish throughout our ride around the lake.  A pair of loons graced us with their presence and singing- and we even saw an otter surface on south side of Big Butternut.

Absolutely gorgeous morning- 69 degrees- full sun- sw wind at 5-6 mph.  Observed 5 eagles hunting- a gaggle of about 25 Canada geese of varying ages- several fishing boats.  Had my two Grandsons helping with secchi disk and temp readings.   Henry and Leo Zuckweiler.
Outstanding day- 76 degrees- sunny- low humidity- west winds 8 mph.  Assisted by daughter in law Margaret Zuckweiler- PE.

Absolutely stunning morning- full sun- west breeze 5 mph.  Observed five loons swimming  in a straight line.  We have seen more loon activity this year than in the previous 30 years.  Saw 8 loons at one time a few weeks ago.  A small private plane flew by our docks at what we considered an unsafe height. If we had been at the end of our dock we could have almost reached out and touched a wing. It did not appear to have any markings- and was not a float plane.

column1: The water clarity and visua perception this summer is outstanding for this lake- compared to years previous.  Maybe it is due to cooler nighttime temps?

column2: Beautiful morning- just a few light clouds- temp 73 wind sw 9 mph.  Feels like we are on a private lake- no other boats out that we could see.   Assisted by Grandsons Henry and Leo.  Observed an eagle diving and coming up with a large fish.  Big Butternut has been exceptionally nice this summer- probably due to cooler overnight temps?  The lake water didn't turn the usual green color until about two weeks ago- which is rare for this lake.  Normally we see a lot of floating algae and green water in early to mid-July at the latest.

Absolutely gorgeous day- sunny- temps about 75.  Saw a winter loon on the lake for the first time.  Not very many Canada geese yet- keeping fingers crossed that they found other neighborhoods to reside.

column1: Helped by Grandsons Henry and Leo.  Temperature meter is not working- so was able to do sechhi disc only.  Water quality is wonderful- like floating on top of an aquarium.

column2: Beautiful morning- winds NE at 7 mph- partly sunny- temp 73.

column1: One fishing boat on lake.   No wildlife this morning.
Assisted by my soulmate- Zoe Zuckweiler.

column2: Absolutely gorgeous day- 77 degrees- blue sky no wind.  Witnessed 80-100 Canada geese swim by around mid morning.
Beautiful summer morning- 74 degrees- full sun- NNW at 3.   3 kayaks on water- 2 loons- 4 fishing boats- no eagle sightings- which is rare.
Fantastic summer day- air temp 79- WNW winds 5 mph- 3 fishing boats on lake- 2 eagles in dead tree by farm.   Two loons observing my activities.
Lake is very low due to lack of rainfall in July and early August.  Water color very green- similar to oil base paint.  One fishing boat out- two loons spotted.   West wind at 5- air temp 81.
Cloudy- 70 degrees- ssw 4mph.  Four fishing boats- one pontoon on lake.  Lake color kind of an irridescent green.

column1: Assisted by Gary Zuckweiler- son- and his able dog Teddy.

column2: Finally got pontoon in the water.  Gorgeous sunny morning- a rarity so far this Spring.  Air temp 65- wind N @ 2mph. Memorial Day weekend- lots of boats on the lake- 2 kayaks and a canoe. Boat finally in water. Air temp 65- wind N @ 2 mph.  Lots of fishing boats and pontoons on the lake- approx. 16.

column1: Two kayaks and a canoe.  Assisted by son in law Tim Wheeler and grandson Joe Wheeler.

column2: Beautiful summer morning- 81 degrees- full sun- no clouds- slight breeze from the south.  7 fishing boats on the lake.  Assisted by my wife- Zoe.
70 degrees- mostly sunny- NE winds at 6 mph.  2 fishing boats on the lake- a loon serenading me as I started out.  Noticed a lot of floating algae particles in the water.

column1: Partly sunny- 75 degrees- wind NNE at 2.   Eagles- herons and ducks active this morning- and lots of boating activity.

Assisted secchi and temp monitoring by son Gary and his wife Margaret.  Fishing has been excellent- with lots of keeper crappies- sunfish and perch.  Grandsons Henry and Leo spending the week doing water sports and hauling in fish for dinner.

column2: Gorgeous sunny morning- 65 degrees- NNW wind at 5 mph.  No other boats on the lake yet.  Assisted by Craig and Cathy Svendsen- our neighbors- and ten of their Grandkids- who are here for a week of fun- science- and discovery. It is an annual event aptly called "Cousins Camp".  The kids names are Owen- Rylee- J.T.- Trevor- Isaac- Mia- Ellie- Emery- Lauren- and Sam.

column1: On the south shore- their are two pontoon boats and lifts overturned from the storm of last Friday- July 19. Many trees were downed during the storm- and the sound of chainsaws around the lake is constant.

column2: Spectacular summer day- 74 degrees- winds WNW at 6- 47% humidity.  Two pontoon boats out- fisherman trying their luck.  Lake water was green floating at north shore line earlier- but looked much better when going out to test.  Middle of lake fine for jumping into.
Beautiful sunny morning- 64 degrees- winds NW 6 mph.  2 fishing boats- 1 pontoon and 1 jet ski on the lake.
63 degrees- WNW winds at 15 mph.  Two fishing boats out- single male loon.  Mostly sunny
Partly sunny- North wind at 4mph- temp 64.  Lots of rain overnight- lake appears to be 3-4? higher- judging by dock bumper.
Beautiful morning- 73 degrees- sunny- NNW winds at 8 mph.  Low humidity.  Perfect.   3 fishing boats out- two flocks of Canada geese- numbering about 25.
Lake was calm- 66 degrees- North breeze at 8 mph.  Mostly sunny skies.  4 fishing boats on the water.  Two helpers this morning-  Henry and Leo- Grandsons.
Partly cloudy- 68 degrees- ESE winds at 2 mph.  7 fishing boats on the lake.  Had over 3" of rain Saturday night- 7/18/20.  Lake surface has a lot of floating algae as a result.

Blue sky- full sun- no clouds. Lake turned over about 4 days ago- following heavy rain. Water very green- lots of floating weeds.  Wind west at 1 mph.  One other pontoon on lake- people fishing. Birds chirping- a few dragonflies.  Per one of my able assistants- Leo.  His brother Henry also helping with water temps and secchi disc.
Beautiful morning- full sun- 68 degrees- wind 1 mph out of South.  No wildlife activity- one fishing boat on the lake.

column1: Water very green- lot of floating algae.
